To install chapi on a machine running the old clearinghouse:

1 - First install the chapidev branch of proto-ch in the usual way (using Makefile.sync on your own laptop and do-make-install.sh on your portal)

2 - Checkout the chapi repository, develop branch on your laptop.

3 - From chapi/chapi/tools, scp the "install_chapi" script to your portal VM

4 - make an empty directory on your portal VM

5 - cd into the new directory and run:
~/install_chapi <VM name e.g. ch-ph.gpolab.bbn.com>

To update the chapi code with a newer version:

1 - From chapi/chapi/tools. scp the "update_chapi" script to your portal VM

2 - make an empty directory on your portal VM

3 - cd into the new directory and run:
~/update_chapi 